This project focused on evaluating the security of a system by identifying its weaknesses and understanding how they could be misused. Through different stages, several issues such as outdated software, weak access controls, and exposed services were discovered. These weaknesses made it possible to gain unauthorized access and view sensitive information. The project highlights how even simple misconfigurations can lead to serious risks if left unaddressed. Overall, it emphasizes the importance of regular security checks, timely updates, and proper system configuration to protect systems from potential threats and ensure a safer digital environment for users and organizations.
